.\" Manpage for simple_shell
.TH simple_shell 3 "April 2021" "Version 1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- interpret and execute lines of commands
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh

[COMMAND] [OPTION]...

.SH DESCRIPTION

simple_shell is a simple implementation of the standard command interpreter for the system that receives comands from the standard input or a file. This version has many features that make it similar in some aspects to the standard shell, but it is
a simple program to learn its operation. Only some standard shell features have been incorporated. 
simple_shell is a program that read commands and arguments given by the user through the standard input and execute them.
When the simple_shell can't find a command or doesn't recognize an option it will print a message error.

.SH INVOCATION
.B simple_shell
may be invoked with the same functionality in
.I interactive
or
.I non-interactive

.SH COMMANDS

.IT
.B Example
.B ls
-list the contents od the directory

.B pwd

- prints the name of the current working directory

.B which

- shows the full path of (shell) commands

.B echo

- shows a line of text

.B Example
.IP

$./hsh

($)pwd

/home/vagrant/simple_shell

($)/bin/pwd

/home/vagrant/simple_shell

($)which ls

/bin/ls

($)echo Hello World

Hello World


.SH BUILT-INS
.B Examples

.B exit
quits the program, exit the shell

.B env
prints the environment variables


